Class TP6

  • java.lang.Object
    • TP6

  • public class TP6
extends java.lang.Object
    The Goal of this exercise is to implement the pattern TopK in a Map-Reduce program, Here we're going to use this pattern to get the most populated cities of the world, based on our file "worldcitiespop.txt" that contains all the cities.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  TP6.TP6Combiner
      The Combiner can be considered as a Mini-Reducer, the biggest difference is that each computer in our Cluster has his own Combiner, and for the Reducer we're working with only one in the whole Cluster.
      static class  TP6.TP6Mapper
      The Mapper will receive a number of lines from the main file, and his role is going to be to extract the top "K" most populated cities, from those he received.
      static class  TP6.TP6Reducer
      The Reducer will receive a number of Lists from the Mappers, and his role is going to be to extract the top "K" most populated cities, from those lists.
